    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Take your <strong>chicken </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-breast-with-yuzu-peppercorn-sauce-and-togarashi-potatoes/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? Use 2 pans or cook in batches!</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>chicken breast portion[s]</strong> and cook for 3 min on each side or until golden</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-breast-with-yuzu-peppercorn-sauce-and-togarashi-potatoes/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>waxy potatoes</strong> to a heatproof bowl, then cover the bowl with <strong>cling film </strong>and pierce a few holes in the top with a fork</p><p>Put the bowl in the microwave for 6-8 min or until the potatoes are fork-tender</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-breast-with-yuzu-peppercorn-sauce-and-togarashi-potatoes/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>roasted garlic paste</strong>, <strong>cracked black pepper </strong>and <strong>yuzu dressing </strong>with your <strong>soft cheese</strong>, <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>and 100ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [130ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[170ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>yuzu stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-breast-with-yuzu-peppercorn-sauce-and-togarashi-potatoes/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken is golden, add the <strong>yuzu stock </strong>to the pan and cook for a further 10-12 min or until the sauce is thickened and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>chicken</strong> <strong>breast with yuzu peppercorn sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-breast-with-yuzu-peppercorn-sauce-and-togarashi-potatoes/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the chicken is cooking, reboil a kettle</p><p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong>, then add to a colander with your <strong>blanched edamame beans</strong></p><p>Pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over it so that the spinach starts to wilt and the edamame beans are warmed through, then drain and squeeze<strong> </strong>any excess water out of the <strong>spinach </strong>with the back of a spoon</p><p>Add a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>to the colander and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>buttery edamame beans & spinach</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-breast-with-yuzu-peppercorn-sauce-and-togarashi-potatoes/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes are fork-tender, add your <strong>shichimi togarashi </strong>to the bowl with a small knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up \u2013 these are your <strong>togarashi potatoes</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-breast-with-yuzu-peppercorn-sauce-and-togarashi-potatoes/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>chicken breast with yuzu peppercorn sauce </strong>with the <strong>togarashi potatoes </strong>and <strong>buttery edamame beans & spinach </strong>to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
